The Proposal: -
Students of different age groups studying in madrassas are brought into the mainstream of the society.
In addition to traditional religious education, science, mathematics, sociology, Hindi, Marathi, English, and Urdu are offered.
Teaching of these subjects, in 9th, 10th, 11th, and 12th grades, etc. for those enrolled in mainstream schools.
Delegation to students studying in industrial training institutes, resulting in student academics.
This is to help improve their economic status by increasing their employability and improving their quality of life.
Infrastructure for modernization of madrassas, grant for library and remuneration to teachers.
